&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Manager– CAMHS Generic and LD Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are very happy to be able to offer an exciting opportunity to become Team Manager for our Haringey CAMHS Generic and LD Teams. Our Generic team is responsible for providing treatment for Moderate to Severe mental health difficulties, our LD team works with YP with LD and Mental health difficulties in the borough. It is an exciting time for CAMHS and we are in the midst of some innovative service and quality improvements. This a new role for somebody with demonstrable skills in both operational management and clinical expertise who can both contribute and lead these changes. This is a golden opportunity for somebody who is ambitious and creative to make a real contribution to improvements in care for young people in the borough. You will need at least 5 years recent experience in CAMHS and a professional registration with the NMC or HCPC to be considered. We will also expect to see good evidence of supervisory experience and CPD throughout your career. In return our fun and friendly teams will provide ample opportunity for learning and development and a varied and interesting environment that rewards someone with good problem solving skills and a positive attitude.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name:Simon Gosling&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Service manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:simon.gosling4@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number:0208 702 4505&lt;/p&gt;
